[Card Formatting Messages][1] page we can see many different `JSON` payloads for different types of cards. On `Github` we can find [Hangouts Chat code samples][2] projects which introduces [`CardResponseBuilder`][3] class which provides some builder methods to build different kind of cards. I think, this is a good approach to do that. If you can, you can try to use this class. It has dependency to `javax.json` library. Using this class and knowing that `Jackson` serialises `Map` to `JSON Object` and `List` to `JSON Array` we can create very similar class:

    class CardResponseBuilder {
    
    	private interface Builder {
