You can get it from two ways.

1) Either you get it from request or session

In JSP Page write following code to get value.

    String value = session.getAttribute(&quot;libelle&quot;); OR
    String value = request.getAttribute(&quot;libelle&quot;);
2) you Can pass value in Ajax Response.

on Servlet write following code.

    out.println(libelle);
and in Ajax you will get data in response.

    $.ajax({
           type: &quot;post&quot;,
           url: &quot;gerer_caf_adherente&quot;,
           data: &quot;name=test&quot;,
           success: function(data){
            alert(data);  // your response will print here.

           }
         });

Your JSP code runs server-side, your JS code runs client-side. They can&#39;t communicate directly, only via HTTP requests.

The request object is a Java abstraction representing a single request. Saving an attribute on a request is just a convenient way to pass data around within the server&#39;s handling of an HTTP request, it is discarded as soon as the request completes ,so you don&#39;t get request attributes after AJAX.But,It doesn&#39;t affect the server&#39;s response to the HTTP request so you can print the data in Response.

To pass information from the server to the client via an AJAX request you must include that information in the response.

So on java side write the data in response using:

    out.println(libelle);

And in Javascript you will be able to get data in response

    $.ajax({
       type: &quot;post&quot;,
       url: &quot;gerer_caf_adherente&quot;,
       data: &quot;name=test&quot;,
       success: function(response){
        alert(response);  // you will see the data in alert, you can use it    anywhere
       }
     });

